The paper focuses on using deep learning for image-based visual servoing in robotic manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves using convolutional neural networks (CNN) for feature extraction and nonlinear relationship estimation from image space to task space, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also proposes a control scheme for the robot manipulator, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SY.
